an now record several sentences of their voice using the Bixby Voice Creator, which then generates an AI copy of their voice to be used for responding to incoming text messages. The generated voice matches the user\'s tone and inflections, providing a more personalized experience for callers.\r\n\r\nThe new feature is currently available in English, with the voice-generator feature only available in Korea. However, Samsung has plans to roll out the voice-generator feature to English speakers with the Galaxy S23 series later this month. The company also intends to make the generated voice compatible with other Samsung apps beyond phone calls.\r\n\r\nWhile the technology may raise concerns about the potential for voice imitation and scams, Samsung has taken measures to alleviate these concerns. Callers are informed that they are speaking to Bixby and not the phone owner. Additionally, the technology has the potential to be useful for individuals with speech impairments or those who struggle to communicate verbally.\r\n\r\nSamsung\'s Bixby Text Call feature is not the only recent development in voice-generating technology. Just last week, Apple patented technology that could allow an iMessage to be read aloud in the sender\'s own voice. As AI technology continues to advance, it is clear that voice-generating systems are becoming more commonplace. In 2023, we are likely to see more advancements in this area and further integration of AI intoeverydaylife.','Samsung Bixby will clone a user\'s voice to answercalls','','publish','open','open','','samsung-bixby-ai-voice-call','','','2023-02-24 10:52:57','2023-02-24 10:52:57','',0,'http://ec2-54-241-199-161.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com/?p=508',0,'post','',0),(509,1,'2023-02-24 10:47:48','2023-02-24 10:47:48','','download2.jpeg','','inherit','open','closed','','download2-jpeg','','','2023-02-24 10:47:48','2023-02-24 10:47:48','',508,'http://ec2-54-241-199-161.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/downlo