r\'s voice to answercalls','','inherit','closed','closed','','508-revision-v1','','','2023-02-24 10:48:11','2023-02-24 10:48:11','',508,'http://ec2-54-241-199-161.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com/?p=510',0,'revision','',0),(511,1,'2023-02-27 09:37:10','2023-02-27 09:37:10','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I am a sportsman turned coder and, learning software development has been one of the most challenging and rewarding experiences of my life. Heres how.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I am naturally an analytical person, who loves to figure out how things run under the hood. This inspired me to grow my skills through problem-solving, creativity, and the challenge of creating something new and innovative. Software development, particularly coding, provided a platform to express this creativity and build something functional and useful, often with immediate feedback on the results.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So how did I begin the most challenging yet rewarding journey in my life?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story began at Edulink Intl College where I was pursuing an Advanced Diploma in Software Engineering before I moved to Middlesex University Dubai where I completed my bachelor\'s degree.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other than programming, my passions lie in football, a sport I have played since I was eight years old. Through hard work, discipline, and grit, I got the opportunity to represent Kenya at the junior level in international tournaments at U17 and U20 levels. And even this enthralling journey through sports didn\'t seem to challenge and push me to the future I envisioned for myself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I believe, there is no greater goal than setting out to challenge oneself and strive to be the best version of myself regardless of whatever field it may be, a</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd so my curiosity was sparked. I set out to learn about the technologies used to build and scale digital products and solutions used by millions of people. I was determined to find my purpose and make my contribution to the evolving technology ecosystem, as well as gain access to how I can integrate my love for football and</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Power Learn Project came at the perfect time for me. It provided a curious footballer with the opportunity to learn about current and applicable technologies in today\'s market. Going through the course content molded me into a competent programmer, able to write clean code in python, javascript, as well as dart, in addition to picking up soft skills that I have used to conceptualize and ideate on my business ventures. Soft skills that you can utilize not just in the software development space but also in other fields as well. This was a stark contrast to other programs I had looked into, which were often outdated and not as relevant to the industry as it is today.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I remember very early on in our python class, we would often be asked by Mr. Stanley Munga to write code with him in the lessons, critique each others code as well as demystify challenging concepts. One thing that definitely stood out for me during these lessons was always being called upon to share my screen and walk other learners through how I was able to come up with my programs.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The program provided a great peer-to-peer learning environment, which allowed me to bounce off the experiences of other learners. My peers brought unique perspectives and skill sets to the table, which made for a well-rounded and diverse learning experience. My peers were also active and engaged participants, who contributed valuable insights and ideas to class discussions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even through the most exciting times of my coding journey, challenges still arose., I found myself being grouped with members who were not as invested as I was, so it definitely was a challenge when we had our hackathons and found ourselves having to collaborate. I remember during one of the hackathons, I found myself sending out our groups GitHub repo for review literally a minute before time was up since two of our members were unable to contribute This showed me that even through uncertain times, powering through many be the only way to get to the other side of my limitless future.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It may not be a U17 or U20 international football tournament yet, but learning software development through the Power Learn Project has been an incredibly thrilling, yet rewarding experience. Difficult in that there is a steep learning curve that can only be overcome through a commitment to your learning journey up until you start to see results. Learning programming is kind of like learning a new language. One thing I always remind myself is that Im always in the process of learning a new language, so I should be patient with myself when something isnt running the way I hoped it would. I am confident that the skills and knowledge I have gained through this program will be invaluable as I continue to grow into my new career as a software developer.</span>\r\n\r\n<em><span class=\"S1PPyQ\">Thoughts by Eric Mureithi, Pioneer Cohort Alumni</span></em>','From Footballer to Developer: How One Sportsman Made the Leap in Just 16 Weeks','','publish','open','open','','from-footballer-to-developer','','','2023-02-27 09:37:10','2023-02-27 09:37:10','',0,'http://ec2-54-241-199-161.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com/?p=511',0,'post','',0),(512,1,'2023-02-27 09:32:47','2023-02-27 09:32:47','','blog banner','','inherit','open','closed','','blog-banner','','','2023-02-27 09:32:47','2023-02-27 09:32:47','',511,'http://ec2-54-241-199-161.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/blog-banner.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(51